IbGuid.name: IbGuid
IbGuid.description: Globally Unique Identifier (GUID) is a number that uniquely identifies an IB device or component. It is a compliant EUI-64 identifier for channel adapter, routers, and switches. This 64-bit value is created by concatenating a 24-bit company ID value and a 40-bit extension. The IEEE Registration Authority assigns the company ID. The extension ID is assigned by the particular company. Therefore, each HCA, TCA, switch, and router shall be assigned an EUI-64 by the manufacturer.

mlxIBCAPCIPhysicalSlot.name: mlxIBCAPCIPhysicalSlot
mlxIBCAPCIPhysicalSlot.description: The PCI (physical) slot of the Channel Adapter. The number zero (0) indicates an embedded interface (on the system board). A value of -1 indicates an interface whose slot is unknown.

mlxIBCAIrq.name: mlxIBCAIrq
mlxIBCAIrq.description: The interrupt request for the Channel Adapter.

mlxIBCAModelString.name: mlxIBCAModelString
mlxIBCAModelString.description: The model string of the Channel Adapter.

mlxIBCASerialNumber.name: mlxIBCASerialNumber
mlxIBCASerialNumber.description: The serial number of the Channel Adapter.

mlxIBCAPartNumber.name: mlxIBCAPartNumber
mlxIBCAPartNumber.description: The part number of the Channel Adapter.

mlxIBCANodeGUID.name: mlxIBCANodeGUID
mlxIBCANodeGUID.description: The NodeGUID of the Channel Adapter. All ports on the same node shall report the same node GUID value. This provides a means for uniquely identifying a CA node within a subnet and helps to determine the co-location of the ports on that CA.

mlxIBCASystemImageGUID.name: mlxIBCASystemImageGUID
mlxIBCASystemImageGUID.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2.1 Vol. 1 Section 14.2.5.6 PortInfo
mlxIBCASystemImageGUID.description: The SystemImageGUID of the Channel Adapter. This GUID associates this node with other nodes controlled by common supervisory code. Provides a means for system software to indicate the availability of multiple paths to the same destination via multiple nodes. Set to zero if indication of node association is not desired. The SystemImageGUID may be the NodeGUID of one of the associated nodes if that node is not field-replaceable.

mlxIBCAFirmwareVersion.name: mlxIBCAFirmwareVersion
mlxIBCAFirmwareVersion.description: The firmware version of the Channel Adapter.

mlxIBCAHardwareVersion.name: mlxIBCAHardwareVersion
mlxIBCAHardwareVersion.description: The hardware version of the Channel Adapter.

mlxIBCAHealthStatus.name: mlxIBCAHealthStatus
mlxIBCAHealthStatus.description: The overall health status of the Channel Adapter.

mlxIBCANumPorts.name: mlxIBCANumPorts
mlxIBCANumPorts.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2.1 Vol. 1 Section 17.2.1.3; Port Attributes and Functions
mlxIBCANumPorts.description: Number of physical IB data ports on this Channel Adapter. Ports are numbered starting from 1. If there is more than one port, the ports are numbered sequentially.

mlxIBCAType.name: mlxIBCAType
mlxIBCAType.description: Type of Channel Adapter; either a Host Channel Adapter (HCA), or a Target Channel Adapter (TCA). The key difference between an HCA and a TCA is that the HCA supports the IBA Verbs layer, while a TCA uses an implementation dependent interface to the transport layer. If the type of CA cannot be determined, the unknown(1) value is returned.

mlxIBPortInfoTableNumPorts.name: mlxIBPortInfoTableNumPorts

mlxIBPortInfoTable.name: mlxIBPortInfoTable
mlxIBPortInfoTable.description: A table containing general information about the IB ports in the system. Holes in this table are possible due to persistent numbering.

mlxIBPortInfoEntry.name: mlxIBPortInfoEntry
mlxIBPortInfoEntry.description: A conceptual row of the mlxIBPortInfoTable containing information about the general characteristics of an IB port in the system.

mlxIBPortIndex.name: mlxIBPortIndex
mlxIBPortIndex.description: Index that identifies the InfiniBand data port in the system. Note that if IB ports are included in MIB-2 ifTable, this can be the same as ifNumber so two different persistent numbering schemes are not needed with translation between the two.

mlxIBPortLocalPortNumber.name: mlxIBPortLocalPortNumber
mlxIBPortLocalPortNumber.description: Index that identifies the InfiniBand data port. IBA defines a range of valid data ports from 1 to N for CAs and router and 0 to N for switches, where N can have a maximum value of 254.

mlxIBPortState.name: mlxIBPortState
mlxIBPortState.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2.1 Vol. 1 Section 14.2.5.6; Table 146 PortInfo
mlxIBPortState.description: The state of the link of this port. Enumerated as: 1 : Down (includes failed links) 2 : Initialize 3 : Armed 4 : Active 5 : Other (0, 5-15: Reserved)

mlxIBPortPhysicalState.name: mlxIBPortPhysicalState
mlxIBPortPhysicalState.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2.1 Vol. 1 Section 14.2.5.6; Table 146 PortInfo
mlxIBPortPhysicalState.description: Physical Port State. Enumerated as: 1 : Sleep 2 : Polling 3 : Disabled 4 : PortConfigurationTraining 5 : LinkUp 6 : LinkErrorRecovery 7 : PhyTest 8 : other (0, 8-15: Reserved)

mlxIBPortGUID.name: mlxIBPortGUID
mlxIBPortGUID.description: The GUID of this IB port. All ports on the same CA shall report a unique mlxIBPortGUID value. This provides a means for uniquely identifying a CA port within a subnet. One port within a node can return the NodeGUID as its PortGUID if the port is an integral part of the node and is not field-replaceable.

mlxIBPortNodeType.name: mlxIBPortNodeType
mlxIBPortNodeType.reference: InfiniBand Architecture Release 1.2.1 Vol. 1 Section 14.2.5.6; Table 146 PortInfo
mlxIBPortNodeType.description: The node type for this port. Enumerated as: 1 : Channel Adapter 2 : Switch 3 : Router 4 : Other (0, 4-15: Reserved)

mlxIBPortNodeIndex.name: mlxIBPortNodeIndex
mlxIBPortNodeIndex.description: Index of the IB node in the mlxIB<NodeType>Table which contains this port.

mlxIBCAHealthStatusChange.name: mlxIBCAHealthStatusChange
mlxIBCAHealthStatusChange.description: The overall health status of the channel adapter has changed. SNMPv1 trap for this has mlxIBNotifications as the enterprise and 1 as the specific trap.

mlxIBCAInsertion.name: mlxIBCAInsertion
mlxIBCAInsertion.description: A channel adapter has been inserted in the system. Insertion of a CA means all its ports have also been inserted (separate port insertion events are not generated). SNMPv1 trap for this has mlxIBNotifications as the enterprise and 2 as the specific trap.

mlxIBCARemoval.name: mlxIBCARemoval
mlxIBCARemoval.description: A channel adapter has been removed from the system. Removal of a CA means all its ports have also been removed (separate port removal events are not generated). SNMPv1 trap for this has mlxIBNotifications as the enterprise and 3 as the specific trap.

mlxIBSwitchInsertion.name: mlxIBSwitchInsertion

mlxIBSwitchRemoval.name: mlxIBSwitchRemoval
mlxIBSwitchRemoval.description: A switch has been removed from the system. Removal of a switch means all its ports have also been removed (separate port removal events are not generated). SNMPv1 trap for this has mlxIBNotifications as the enterprise and 5 as the specific trap.

mlxIBRouterInsertion.name: mlxIBRouterInsertion
mlxIBRouterInsertion.description: A router has been inserted in the system. Insertion of a router means all its ports have also been inserted (separate port insertion events are not generated). SNMPv1 trap for this has mlxIBNotifications as the enterprise and 6 as the specific trap.

mlxIBRouterRemoval.name: mlxIBRouterRemoval
mlxIBRouterRemoval.description: A router has been removed from the system. Removal of a router means all its ports have also been removed (separate port removal events are not generated). SNMPv1 trap for this has mlxIBNotifications as the enterprise and 7 as the specific trap.

mlxIBPortStateChange.name: mlxIBPortStateChange
mlxIBPortStateChange.description: The port state has changed. Refer to mlxIBPortState. SNMPv1 trap for this has mlxIBNotifications as the enterprise and 8 as the specific trap.

mlxIBPortPhysicalStateChange.name: mlxIBPortPhysicalStateChange
mlxIBPortPhysicalStateChange.description: The physical port state has changed. Refer to mlxIBPortPhysicalState. SNMPv1 trap for this has mlxIBNotifications as the enterprise and 9 as the specific trap.

mlxIBPortInsertion.name: mlxIBPortInsertion
mlxIBPortInsertion.description: An IBA port has been inserted in the system. SNMPv1 trap for this has mlxIBNotifications as the enterprise and 10 as the specific trap.

mlxIBPortRemoval.name: mlxIBPortRemoval
mlxIBPortRemoval.description: An IB port has been removed from the system. SNMPv1 trap for this has mlxIBNotifications as the enterprise and 11 as the specific trap.
